This paper presents a new lock-free data structure for hash tables, which is a fundamental topic in computer science and falls under the category of data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance and scalability of the proposed data structure, which involves parallel computing and distributed systems, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the implementation of the algorithm in C++, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the progress guarantees of the algorithm, which is related to control theory and system dynamics, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of the proposed algorithm with other existing algorithms, which falls under cs.PF (Performance).
